description: From fig (“to move briskly; go to and fro”, a variant of fike) +‎ -le (frequentative suffix). Compare also Middle English fikelen (“to wag the head or tail; fawn”).

verbs.description: figgle (third-person singular simple present figgles, present participle figgling, simple past and past participle figgled)

entries.meaning: (intransitive, Northern England) To fidget about; wriggle
(intransitive, Northern England) To potter about seeking a living
